## Iteration 1 Hypotheses

1. Accepted hypotheses
Students need a centralized course information system due to fragmented information across multiple platforms.
Students require filtering and comparison tools to improve elective selection efficiency.
International students need additional onboarding and system guidance due to unfamiliarity.
Students need decision support to help align course selection with career goals.

2. Refuted / weak hypotheses
Manual enrollment errors (e.g. missing or conflicting courses) are not a primary pain point.
Fully automated course enrollment is not a key requirement; students prioritise decision support and clarity instead.

